## Conclusion

The AlphaFold-based *ab initio* prediction successfully generated a plausible structural model for KLB. The predicted structure revealed stable extracellular core domains together with flexible terminal regions, consistent with the dynamic signaling role of the protein.

This study demonstrates how computational modeling can provide valuable structural insight into proteins with limited experimentally resolved data.
